replies.bodyText:
Yes, you are right, but the reason I am suggesting to bring back these variables is because of two reasons.

It will improve the performance of the application - since these are final variables, they will be only calculated once and JVM will optimize the runtime code by replacing their actual values.
It will be much easier to read the code that way - as it is much simpler to read the instance variables as compared to calling APIs.

In my opinion, we should bring them back in CosmosTemplate and ReactiveCosmosTemplate
    private final String databaseName;
    private final ResponseDiagnosticsProcessor responseDiagnosticsProcessor;
    private final boolean enableQueryMetrics;

What are your thoughts on the above reasons?

